HEADWORD: Mammuthus primigenius
<hw>Mammuthus primigenius</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The species name for the woolly mammoth, a very hairy mammoth
common in colder portions of the Northern hemisphere.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> woolly mammoth, northern mammoth.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mammutidae</ent>⟦br⟧
